Z.ai ships GLM-5.2 open-weight model with 1M context and stronger coding
7,577 Likes
Z.ai just dropped
GLM-5.2
, an open-weights model built for serious coding work. Here is what makes i=
t interesting.
The biggest upgrade is the context window.
1 million tokens
means you can feed it an entire codebase in one shot and ask it to refactor=
, debug, or extend it without losing track. That jumped 5x from GLM-5.1's 2=
00K limit.
You also get two reasoning modes to control speed vs. quality tradeoffs:
Max mode
: pushes hardest on complex problems, uses more compute
High mode
: faster and cheaper, still strong for most tasks
MIT license
: download the weights, self-host it, fine-tune it, ship it commercially, n=
o strings attached
Benchmark scores
: 81.0 on Terminal-Bench 2.1, up from 62.0 on GLM-5.1
On pricing, it runs at $1.40 per million input tokens, roughly one-sixth of=
 GPT-5.5. You can grab the weights on Hugging Face or hit the Z.ai API dire=
ctly.
