Cursor announces Origin, a git hosting platform built for AI agents
6,114 Likes
Cursor just announced
Origin
, their own git hosting platform, and it's a direct shot at GitHub.
Here's the quick backstory: Cursor (the AI code editor) acquired Graphite, =
a code review tool, and now they're stacking a full hosting layer on top. T=
he goal is to own the entire coding pipeline, write in Cursor, review with =
Graphite, host on Origin.
So why does this matter? AI agents are now opening pull requests (proposed =
code changes) faster than humans can review them.
GitHub was built for humans
, not for dozens of AI agents committing code in parallel. A live demo show=
ed
22.6 commits per second
inside a single repo, a load GitHub was never designed for.
Origin is built specifically for that world. Key features include:
Scales to handle massive agent-driven commit volumes
Built-in merge conflict resolution handled automatically by agents
Extensible via
API and MCP
(a standard way for AI tools to talk to each other)
Native integration with Cursor's existing agent workflows
You can join the waitlist now. Full release is coming this fall.
