Nous Research's Hermes agent can now buy things and pay APIs using Stripe
4,729 Likes
Your AI agent just got a wallet.
Hermes Agent
now has three official Stripe skills, and together they let your agent hand=
le real money, on its own, with guardrails you control.
Here is what you can install:
stripe-link-cli
-- lets your agent buy things on the open web, like a human clicking checko=
ut
mpp-agent
-- lets your agent pay for APIs that charge per call, so it can keep workin=
g without stopping to ask you for a credit card
stripe-projects
-- lets your agent spin up and bill its own SaaS products, no human require=
d
To get any of these, run: hermes skills install official/payments/[skill-na=
me]
The safety story matters here.
Your real credentials never appear in the agent's conversation history.
You can require human approval before any payment fires. One-time credentia=
ls are deleted after use. Stripe Projects issues scoped credentials tied to=
 a specific project, with pre-defined permissions and spending guardrails.
What this opens up: agents that fund themselves, pay for their own tools, a=
nd ship products, all while you stay in control of the limits.
